Travel Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Anything which is not include in the inclusion</li>\r\n	<li>3.625 % Govt. Service Tax Extra</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '50% of the package cost at the time of booking confirmation.<br />\r\nBalace 50% of the package cost 8 days prior to the travel date.', '<ul>\r\n	<li>From booking date till 21 Days prior to departure : 25% of the Total Package Cost</li>\r\n	<li>From 21 Days to 14 Days prior to departure : 50% of the Total Package Cost</li>\r\n	<li>From 14 Days to 07 Days prior to departure : 100% of the Total Package Cost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>Important :</strong> The booking stands liable to be cancelled if 100% payment is not received less than 07 days before date of departure.</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<strong>Day 01:&nbsp; Bagdogra/NJP to Gangtok 125 kms 4 hours approx.</strong><br />\r\nAssistance at the airport/railway station on arrival and drive to Gangtok.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Gangtok : </strong>At an altitude of 1750m, Gangtok became the state capital in the mid 19th century and has undergone rapid development since then. The downtown area is dominated by huge government buildings decorated with traditional Buddhist symbols. Gangtok is also a resting ground for people traveling to North Sikkim. Surrounded by Monasteries and Orchids, Gangtok is truly a travellers delight. Overnight at hotel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 02:&nbsp; Gangtok</strong><br />\r\nBreakfast at the hotel and full day excursion to Changu Lake which is 35 Kms from Gangtok at an altitude of 12,400 feet. The lake derives its waters from melting snows off the surrounding mountains Legends say that lamas could forecast the future by studying the color of the lake&rsquo;s waters. Also visit Baba Mandir .Overnight at hotel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Day 03:&nbsp; Gangtok &ndash; Lachen 123 kms 6 hours approx.</strong><br />\r\nBreakfast at the hotel in Gangtok and drive to Lachen enroute visiting villages and water falls,Overnight at hotel.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Day 04:&nbsp; Lachen -- Gurudongma -- Lachung </strong><br />\r\nBreakfast at the hotel and excursion to Gurudongma Lake &amp; back to Lachung. - The valley of flowers.&nbsp; Flora, Fauna, Rhododendrons and Primulas and found in abundance.&nbsp; Yumthang is the summer grazing grounds of the Yaks.&nbsp; On the way back visit the Sulphur Hot Spring, considered to have medicinal properties. Overnight at hotel<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Day 05:&nbsp; Lachung &ndash; Yumthang &ndash; Gangtok</strong><br />\r\nBreakfast at the hotel and visit Yumthang Valley, Hot Spring, &nbsp;and drive back to Gangtok enroute visit Twin Falls, Bhim Nala etc.,Overnight at hotel in Gangtok.<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Day 06 : Gangtok &ndash; Bagdogra/NJP</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;Breakfast at the hotel and drive to Bagdogra/NJP in time for flight/train to onward destination<strong>Day 01:&nbsp; Bagdogra/NJP to Gangtok 125 kms 4 hours approx.</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nAssistance at the airport/railway station on arrival and drive to Gangtok.<br />\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</h2>\r\n', '<div class="row informaiton">\r\n<div id="pkgOverView">\r\n<p>Travel to Darjeeling, Gangtok, Lachung &amp; Lachen this summer to experience the glory of the Himalayas. View the majestic Kanchandzonga, drive to the high altitude Tsomgo Lake and visit Buddhist monasteries that dot the region. See the beauty of the Yumthang Valley unfold as you drive past sturdy mountains and blooming pastures. In the North East, there is never a dull moment.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n', '2016-03-26', 1, 'Y', 'Deal', 'North East 05Night /06Day', '<meta name="robots" content="follow, index, all" />\r\n<meta name="google-site-verification" content="rd73NCmbOEiQ6HB6_UKxP0zkp9V5u4A