rjeeling-overnight at darjeeling.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>DAY 04: Darjeeling&nbsp; Sightseeing</strong><br />\r\nEarly Morning (at 4.00 am) drive to Tiger Hill to watch the spectacular Sunrise over Mt. Khangchendzongha (28,208 ft.&nbsp;Worlds 3rd highest peak), on your way back visit Ghoom Monastery and Batasia Loop. After breakfast visit Himalayan Mountaineering Institute, P.N. Zoological Park (Thursday closed), Tenzing Rock, Tibetan Refugee Self-help Centre (Sunday closed), Tea Garden (outer view), Ava Art Gallery and Japanese Temple (4 hrs from 9.00 to 13.00 hrs). Evening free for shopping &amp; leisure. Overnight stay at Darjeeling.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>DAY 05: Darjeeling &ndash; Bagdogra/NJP<br />\r\nBack to Sweet Home with Lovely memory</strong> After breakfast check out from hotel on time and take the departure transfer to IXB Airport for your onward journey.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;', 'North East offers the tourists a unique journey. Gangtok, offers a beautiful sight of the Tsomgo Lake. Along with it, Gangtok tours also offer a visit to the magnificent monasteries and provide a great shopping experience in ever shining markets. Darjeeling, with expansive tea estates and ride via Toy train, the world heritage site; Darjeeling Tours offers the tourists with some fun-filled moments to remember. With third highest mountain ranges, Kanchenjunga also included in the Hills Tour, trekkers will have fun-filled trips.', '2016-07-28', 1, 'Y', 'Hot Deal', 'Majestic North East 04Night/05DAY for Summer', '<meta name="robots" content="follow, index, all" />\r\n<meta name="google-site-verification" content="rd73NCmbOEiQ6HB6_UKxP0zkp9V5u4A0jUCxH1fyMW0" />\r\n<meta name="msvalidate.01" content="D29D07AB3800231EE10F0FD2410E816A" />\r\n<meta name="distribution" content="Global" />\r\n<meta name="doc-type" content="Public"/>\r\n<meta name="classification" content="travel" />\r\n<meta property="og:title" content="North East Holiday Packages - Book North East Packages, N