in Fare</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance Fees, parking &amp; Guide charges</li>\r\n	<li>Any personal expensive &ndash; laundry , shopping, tip etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Meal other than specified</li>\r\n	<li>Monument entrance fee / Camera fees</li>\r\n	<li>Travel Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Anything which is not include in the inclusion</li>\r\n	<li><strong>3.625 %</strong> Govt. Service Tax Extra</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul class="list">\r\n	<li>50% of the package cost at the time of booking confirmation.</li>\r\n	<li>Balance 50% of the package cost 8 days prior to the travel date.</li>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<li><strong>Important :</strong>The booking stands liable to be cancelled if 100% payment is not received less than 08 days before date of departure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul class="list">\r\n	<li>From booking date till 21 Days prior to departure : 25% of the Total Package Cost</li>\r\n	<li>From 21 Days to 14 Days prior to departure : 50% of the Total Package Cost</li>\r\n	<li>From 14 Days to 08 Days prior to departure : 100% of the Total Package Cost</li>\r\n	<li><strong>All booking vouchers and tickets will be provided 3 days before departure.</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<strong>Day 01: Paro Airport&ndash; Thimphu (188 kms / 7 hr)</strong><br />\r\nPick up from Paro Airport and after completing the immigration formalities transfer to Thimphu (7,710 ft.) the capital city of Bhutan. On arrival check in at the hotel.and leisure time in Town.Overnight &nbsp;at Thimphu.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 02: Thimphu Sightseeing</strong><br />\r\nThimphu the capital of Bhutan is a home of Royal family. After breakfast visit Tashichhodzong ,the main secretariat building which houses the throne room of His Majesty,the king. View of the Thimphu valley from BBS Tower is very captivating and will prove to be the perfect introduction to Thimphu. &nbsp;Some of the sites of religious nature are National Memorial Chorten; built in 1974 it was raised in the memory of third King. &nbsp;Next visit one of the oldest monasteries in the valley- Chang Gangkha Monastery. &nbsp;The nature and wildlife lovers should not miss a visit to National Zoo which also houses national animal takin. &nbsp; National Library (collections of holy scripts) &amp; in the evening visit &nbsp;Buddha point. Get indulged into Weekend Local Market. Overnight &nbsp;at Thimphu.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 03: Thimphu &ndash; Punakha / Wangdue Sightseeing (77 kms / 3 hrs)</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast drive to Punakha / Wangdue Phodrang (4,300 ft.), via Dochu-La-Pass (10,170 ft.). Continue towards Punakha visit Chimi Lhakhang - The Temple of Fertility built in 15th century. Also visit Punakha Dzong. On arrival check in at the hotel. Evening free for leisure. Overnight &nbsp;at Punakha.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\n<strong>Day 04: Punakha &ndash; Paro (140 kms / 5 hrs)</strong><br />\r\nVisit the Ta Dzong, once a fortified lookout tower that is now the National Museum. Then walk down the trail to visit the Rinpung Dzong meaning &quot;fortress of the heap of jewels&quot;. Next visit Kichu Lhakhang, the oldest temple in the country. From there you will be taken to the Drugyal Dzong (Bhutan Victory Fort), which was built in 1646 to commemorate Bhutan&#39;s victory over Tibetan invaders during the 1600s. On a clear day you can see Mount Jumolhari, Bhutan&#39;s second-highest mountain at 7,314meters. Evening is free for leisure. Overnight &nbsp;at Paro.<br />\r\nor&nbsp;<br />\r\nAfter breakfast hike to Taktsang (Tiger&#39;s Nest) Monastery, which is Bhutan&#39;s most famous monastery situated at 3180 meters. Guru Rinpoche (the great spiritual master) is said to have flown on the back of a tigress to meditate in a cave where Taktsang Monastery now stands. The monastery is perched on the edge of a steep cliff, about 900 meters above Paro Valley.. Overnight &nbsp;at Paro.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<strong>Day 05: Paro &ndash; Airport Drop&nbsp;</strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out from hotel and drop to Paro Airport for the onward Journey.<br />\r\n&nbsp;', 'Travel Bhutan with Bhutan Travel Packages and explore the mighty Himalayan range, pristine freshwater lakes, nature trails, exotic treks, ancient monasteries, historical fortresses one feels is the amalgamation of two very separate spheres, the traditional and the modern world; people of Bhutan are deeply religious but at the same time don&#39;t shun away modern amenities.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '2016-07-31', 1, 'Y', 'Online Special', 'Delightful Bhutan Summer Special', '<meta name="robots" content="follow, index, all" />\r\n<meta name="google-site-verification" content="rd73NCmbOEiQ6HB6_UKxP0zkp9V5u4A0jUCxH1fyMW0" />\r\n<meta name="msvalidate.01" content="D29D07AB3800231EE10F0FD2410E816A" />\r\n<meta name="distribution" content="Global" />\r\n<meta name="doc-type" content="Public"/>\r\n<meta name="classification" content="travel" />\r\n<meta property="og:title" content="Bhutan Holiday Packages - Book Bhutan Packages, Bhutan Vacations and Tour Packages with MyTravelDesk.in, India" />', 'Bhutan Holiday Packages - Book Bhutan Packages, Bhutan Vacations and Tour Packages with MyTravelDesk.in, India', 'Delightful Bhutan, Summer Special Bhutan, Bhutan Tour, Bhutan Package, Best Deal on Bhutan Holiday', 'Y', '2016-03-03 08:32:36', '2016-03-03 03:02:36'),
