 Tiger Hill to view sunrise over Kanchendzonga Peak (subject to clear weather) &ndash; On the way back visit Ghoom Monastery, Peace memorial &amp; Batasia Loop &ndash; On the way back visit Ghoom Monastery, Peace memorial &amp; Batasia Loop &ndash; Back to hotel for breakfast - After breakfast rest for half an hour After breakfast next round of sight seeing - Half Day city tour includes Padmaja Naidu Zoological Park, Himalayan Mountaineering Institute (Closed on Thursday), Ropeway, Tensing Gumpo Rock, Tibetan Refugee Self Help Center (Closed on Sunday), Tea Estate, Natural History Museum (Sunday Closed), Peace Pagoda &ndash; Back to hotel &ndash; Evening free to stroll around the area - Overnight stay at Darjeeling<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;<strong>Day 3: Transfer to Kalimpong &amp; Sightseeing at Kalimpong</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nEarly morning Breakfast - After breakfast drive 65 kilometers 1 &frac12; - 2 hours transfer to the Kalimpong - Kalimpong situated on the foothills of the Himalayas is a green destination at an altitude of 1243 meters / 4078 feet - It is a historical destinations with bustling market, colorful people and offers spectacular views of the Himalayan range &ndash; Check into hotel &ndash; Drive for sight seeing tour through scenic road to Forest Museum (Closed On Thursday), Deolo Hill, Hanuman Mandir, Dr Graham Homes, Durbin Monastery, Mangaldham, Pine View Nurseries (Cactus Only) - Back to Kalimpong Hotel &ndash; Evening free to roam around the any of the hundred nurseries or the Local market area - Overnight stay at Kalimpong<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&nbsp;<strong>Day 4: Departure</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nKalimpong to Siliguri / New Jalpaiguri Railway Station (NJP) / Bagdogra Airport (IXB) / Tenzing Norgay Bus Stand (Junction) - Morning breakfast - After breakfast transfer to Siliguri / New Jalpaiguri Railway Station (NJP) / Bagdogra Airport (IXB) / Tenzing Norgay Bus Stand (Junction) - Nearly 100 kilometers 3 &frac12; hours drive &ndash; Forwarding Journey', 'If you want to see nature&#39;s real beauty then a visit to North East India is a must. Consisting of 7 states also called &#39;Seven Sisters&#39; North East India has some real surprises for the travelers coming here. Not so much established on the travelers map, yet the North Eastern India, has its own charm that will sweep you off your feet. Come here for once and loose yourself in its charismatic magic.<br />\r\n&nbsp;', '2016-07-27', 5, 'Y', 'North East Delight with Kalimpong  03 Night / 04 Day', 'North East Delight with Kalimpong  03 Night / 04 Day', 'North East Delight with Kalimpong  03 Night / 04 Day', 'North East Delight with Kalimpong  03 Night/ 04 Day', 'North East Delight with Kalimpong  03 Night / 04 Day', 'Y', '2016-03-03 12:54:58', '2016-03-03 07:24:58'),
(32, 'Mini Kerala 04N/05D Summer Special', 15000, '2016-03-07', '2016-07-30', 5, 4, 2, '<ul class="list">\r\n	<li>Per person rates (in Rs.) - applicable on 2 persons (or as mentioned in Itinerary) staying together sharing the same room</li>\r\n	<li>Service Tax extra (as applicable)</li>\r\n	<li>Transportation as per itinerary only (not available at disposal)</li>\r\n	<li>The package does not include guide services. These can be availed at an additional cost</li>\r\n	<li>Package rates &amp; Availability are subject to change without prior notice</li>\r\n	<li>Meal plan: EP - Accommodation only, CP - Accommodation with breakfast, MAP - Accommodation with breakfast, lunch or dinner, AP - Accommodation with breakfast, lunch and dinner</li>\r\n	<li>The package cannot be combined with any other offer</li>\r\n	<li>Refund on cancellation depends upon concerned hotel&#39;s cancellation policy</li>\r\n	<li>The above package is not valid during national holidays, festivals, long weekends and New Year</li>\r\n	<li>We are not responsible for any loss / delay / rescheduling of trip &amp; escalation of cost due to Natural Calamities (Earthquake, Flood, Land-sliding etc.)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '', '<ul>\r\n	<li>02 Night Accommodation in Munnar Hotel Deluxe on twin sharing basis as per the Itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>01 Night Accommodation in Alleppey Hotel Deluxe on twin sharing basis as per the Itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>Buffet Breakfast.</li>\r\n	<li>Assistance on arrival and departure at Airport/Railway station by MyTravelDesk representative</li>\r\n	<li>Sight-seeing as per itinerary.</li>\r\n	<li>All Transportation for local sight-seeing tours and airport/ hotel by A/C vehicle as per Itinerary.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul class="exc_list">\r\n	<li>Airfare &amp; Train Fare</li>\r\n	<li>Entrance Fees, parking &amp; Guide charges</li>\r\n	<li>Any personal expensive &ndash; laundry , shopping, tip etc.</li>\r\n	<li>Meal other than specified</li>\r\n	<li>Monument entrance fee / Camera fees</li>\r\n	<li>Travel Insurance</li>\r\n	<li>Anything which is not include in the inclusion</li>\r\n	<li>3.625 % Govt. Service Tax Extra</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul class="list">\r\n	<li>50% of the package cost at the time of booking confirmation.</li>\r\n	<li>Balance 50% of the package cost 8 days prior to the travel date.</li>\r\n	<br />\r\n	<li><strong>Important :</strong>The booking stands liable to be cancelled if 100% payment is not received less than 08 days before date of departure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '<ul class="list">\r\n	<li>From booking date till 21 Days prior to departure : 25% of the Total Package Cost</li>\r\n	<li>From 21 Days to 14 Days prior to departure : 50% of the Total Package Cost</li>\r\n	<li>From 14 Days to 08 Days prior to departure : 100% of the Total Package Cost</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<strong>All booking vouchers and tickets will be provided 3 days before departure.</strong>', 'Day 1: Arrive Cochin &ndash; Munnar<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAssistance at the airport on arrival and drive to Munnar<br />\r\nMunnar: On arrival at Cochin Airport Transfer to Munnar . En route visit Cheyapara &amp; vallara waterfalls. Later Check into hotel. Proceed for the Sightseeing of Munnar Town, Tea Museum Blossom Park, Rose Garden Etc .Over Night Stay at Hotel in Munnar.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 2: Munnar Sightseeing&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><br />\r\nAfter breakfast spend the day with local sightseeing. Situated at the confluence of three mountain streams - Mudrapuzha, Nallathanni and Kundale, Munnar is 1600 Meter above sea level. This majestic hill station was once the summer resort of the British government in South India. Local sightseeing of Munnar includes visit to Mattupetty Dam, Kundale Lake and Echo point. Afternoon proceed to Rajamalai were the rarest species of mountain goat, &quot;Nilgiri Thars&quot;, can be spotted. Overnight stay is arranged at Munnar.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 3: Munnar &ndash; Thekkady<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out from the hotel and drive to Thekkady (3 Hrs); on arrival check in to the hotel. Proceed for the sightseeing tour of Thekkady - one of the world&#39;s most fascinating wild life reserves. The Periyar wild life sanctuary in Thekkady is spread across 777 sq km of which 360 sq km is thick ever green forest. Noted for its geomorphology, diversity of wild life and scenic beauty, the sanctuary was declared a Tiger Reserve in 1978. Optional activities like Boating at Periyar Lake, Spice Plantation visit and Elephant Ride can be done at an extra cost. Overnight stay is arranged in Thekkady.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 4: Thekkady &ndash; Alleppey<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out and proceed to Alleppey (3.5 hrs); which is famous for its backwater &amp; scenic beauty, sprinkled with traditional hotel, On arrival check in at the Hotel. Later proceed to&nbsp; enjoy the&nbsp; Kerala Backwaters or optional proceed for a backwater cruise (on extra cost) to experience the Lake and by evening enjoy the sun set at Alleppey beach and evening proceed to hotel. Stay overnight at Alleppey.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nDay 5: Cochin Drop<br />\r\n<br />\r\nAfter breakfast check out from the hotel and drive to Cochin/ railway station (depend on your departure place) for your flight / train back home, feeling contented about a wonderful holiday you spent in the God&rsquo;s Own Country. Tour Ends.<br />\r\n&nbsp;', 'A sliver of a coastal state in India&#39;s deep south, Kerala is shaped by its layered landscape: almost 600km of glorious Arabian Sea coast and beaches; a languid network of glistening backwaters; and the spice and tea-covered hills of the Western Ghats. Just setting foot on this swathe of soul-quenching, palm-shaded green will slow your subcontinental stride to a blissed-out amble. Kerala is a world away from the frenzy of elsewhere, as if India had passed through the Looking Glass and become an altogether more laid-back place.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nBesides its famous backwaters, elegant houseboats, ayurvedic treatments and delicately spiced, taste-bud-tingling cuisine, Kerala is home to wild elephants, exotic birds and the odd tiger, while vibrant traditions such as Kathakali plays, temple festivals and snake-boat races frequently bring even the smallest villages to life. It&#39;s hard to deny Kerala&#39;s liberal use of the slogan &#39;God&#39;s Own Country&#39;', '2016-07-24', 1, 'Y', 'Mini Kerala 04N/05D Summer Special', 'Mini Kerala 04N/05D Summer Special', 'Mini Kerala 04N/05D Summer Special', 'Mini Kerala 04N/05D Summer Special', 'Mini Kerala 04N/05D Summer Special', 'Y', '2016-03-03 12:03:25', '2016-03-03 06:33:25');
